abstractText: Habitat restoration projects often include planting trees and shrubs and/or creating conditions to facilitate natural recruitment of woody vegetation. Evaluating the establishment of woody vegetation cover in a project area can be used to evaluate whether project objectives are being achieved, such as establishing woody vegetation cover in a project area.Data collection methods are described in Floodplain Woody Vegetation Composition and Percent Cover Method #1183 [https://www.monitoringresources.org/Document/Method/Details/1183].
title: Floodplain Woody Vegetation Composition and Percent Cover Analysis v1.0
